'''Elizabeth Rummel''' ("Lizzie"; born 19 February 1897 in [[Munich]];<ref>{{cite web|title=Who is Lizzie Rummel?|url=http://ers.crps.ca/Who%20is%20Lizzie%20Rummel.php|website=Elizabeth Rummel School|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> died 1980) was a [[German-Canadian]] [[environmentalist]]. In 1980, she was made a Member of the [[Order of Canada]] for her [[mountaineering]] and environmental contributions, and "enrich[ing] her [[Canada|country]] by sharing her deep love of the [[Rocky Mountains]] with all who meet her."<ref>{{cite web|title=Order of Canada - Elizabeth Rummel, C.M.|url=http://archive.gg.ca/honours/search-recherche/honours-desc.asp?lang=e&TypeID=orc&id=2277|website=Governor General of Canada - Archives|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref>

