[[File:The Fawley Tunnel - geograph.org.uk - 1590531.jpg|thumb|A fenced-off entrance to the tunnel]]
'''Fawley Tunnel''' is a {{Convert|3|m|adj=on}} diameter, {{Convert|2|mi|adj=on}} long tunnel under [[Southampton Water]] between [[Fawley Power Station]] and Chilling near [[Warsash]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Ian|first=West|title=Geology of Fawley Power Station Excavations|url=http://www.southampton.ac.uk/~imw/Fawley-Power-Station-geology.htm|accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> It was constructed between 1962 and 1965 to carry two 400 kV circuits as part of the [[National Grid (Great Britain)|National Grid]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Scope for Undergrounding Overhead Electricity Lines|url=http://warrington.ufl.edu/purc/docs/initiatives_HH_2002LakeDistrict_ScopeUnderground.pdf|accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref>

