'''Traumatin''' is a [[plant hormone]] produced in response to wound.<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1104/pp.63.3.536 |vauthors=Zimmerman DC, Coudron CA |title=Identification of Traumatin, a Wound Hormone, as 12-Oxo-trans-10-dodecenoic Acid |journal= Plant Physiology|volume=63 |issue=3 |pages=536–541 |year=1979 |pmid=16660762 |url=http://www.plantphysiol.org/cgi/reprint/63/3/536.pdf |publisher=[[Plant Physiology (journal)|Plant Physiology]] |pmc=542865}}</ref>  Traumatin is a precursor to the related hormone [[traumatic acid]].

